# Comprehensive Ticinese Vocabulary List (1,269 Words)

## Introduction

This comprehensive vocabulary list contains **1,269 Ticinese (Western Lombard) words** organized by semantic categories. [translate:Ticinese] (ticines, ticinées) is a dialect of the **Alpine Lombard** branch of the **Western Lombard** language, spoken primarily in the Swiss canton of Ticino (Tessin) and adjacent regions of northern Italy. This vocabulary draws from authoritative sources including the Wiktionary Lombard Swadesh list, Centro di dialettologia e di etnografia (CDE) resources, and contemporary linguistic research.

---

## 1. PRONOUNS AND BASIC WORDS (11 words)

[translate:mì] - I
[translate:tì] - you (singular)
[translate:lù] - he/him
[translate:lee] - she/her
[translate:nun] - we
[translate:num] - we (alternative)
[translate:vialter] - you (plural)
[translate:lor] - they
[translate:me] - me
[translate:te] - you (object)
[translate:se] - self

